econd common but considerably more expensive solution is high - quality, high - capacity ceramic tiles. If you succeed in choosing the right variety, the deficiencies will be minimum. Tiles are expensive and the installation is resource - intensive. Also they are resistant to spilled water or chemicals and are easy to maintain. With the occasional sweeping or wiping down, they last for decades &ndash; if installed properly.</p>\r\n<p>But even a well - laid tile floor can become worse. Practically every floor in the garage can handle summer conditions, but with winter comes the problems. Above all, it&rsquo;s the capillary action of bottom water, which gets beneath it causing foul - smell and makes the surface to swell.</p>\r\n<p>Another problem with ceramic tiles is their brittleness. It will take just a few times before a heavy tool falls from your hands and the first tile is cracked. And talking about slipperiness, if you choose a tile with a glossy surface (glazed), you can bet they will become slippery in wintertime.</p>\r\n<h2>PVC floor tiles - improving the properties of ceramic tiles</h2>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog8-1.png\" alt=\"why to choose pvc tile for garage\"></figure>\r\n<p>In order to improve the properties of ceramic tiles, production began on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/fortelock.php\">pvc floor tiles</a>&nbsp;, which are especially good for garages, workshops or industrial buildings. The locking sections are snapped together with a rubber hammer. The surface must first be leveled and swept, then it&rsquo;s a piece of cake. It takes roughly an hour to cover an averagely large garage.</p>\r\n<blockquote>To know more, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/rhino-floor-tiles-in-industrial-use.php\">Where does Rhino Floor Tiles excel in Industrial use?</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>The locking pieces of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/\">floor tiles</a>&nbsp;are so tight that no water can get under them. However if that happens, it will simply evaporate because the tile &ldquo;breathes&rdquo;. They are resistant to chemicals and acids, and unlike ceramic tiles do not become slippery (they have an anti - slip design). And if any one tile is damaged, it can be replaced individually.</p>\r\n<h2>What floor goes best in a garage?</h2>\r\n<p>That depends on each person. Some prefer a low price, and so choose painting. Others don&rsquo;t want to go with classical methods and choose tiles. They&rsquo;re not afraid of modern innovation and so reach for PVC floor tiles. Rhino floor provides the best&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/garages.php\">garage flooring tiles</a>. We have presented the advantages and disadvantages, and now it&rsquo;s up to you to decide whether to go with a cheap solution, or rather a reliable and long - term one.</p>\r\n<p>For more details, drop us a mail -&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:sales@rhinofloor.ae\">sales@rhinofloor.ae</a></p>','Garage Flooring - Benefits of PVC tiles over paint and ceramic tiles','Choose a Multi-coloured design for your Garage. See how beneficial colored tiles can be compared to paint & ceramic tiles. Reliable & long-term solution.','pvcfloortiles, floortiles, garageflooringtiles','in-the-process-of-choosing-a-floor-for-your-garage','blogs/in-the-process-of-choosing-a-floor-for-your-garage_default_1704690664.png','UAE floor tiles',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2024-01-08 17:41:05','2024-01-08 17:41:05'),(37,2,'What type of flooring is affordable and most preferable for a laundry room?',NULL,'<h1>What type of flooring is affordable and most preferable for a laundry room?</h1>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog9.png\" alt=\"best laundry floor tiles, laundry flooring options\"></figure>\r\n<p>Whether you have a laundry room as a separate room in your home or you are trying to improve the common laundry room in an apartment building, it requires a special floor. It can be compared with a bathroom since you deal with moisture and dampness there, but it&rsquo;s rather more a working space than one where you can relax. This implies that the way it works is more important than its design.</p>\r\n<h2>Which floor should it be?</h2>\r\n<p>The first question to be considered is about what properties the floor in the laundry room should have and what you can expect from it. The answer is quite clear. Most important is its resistance to water and moisture. If you also use the room for drying, then you can expect water to drip from the wet laundry. That could damage certain types of floors. A wet floor could even harm you. Slipping with a full basket of laundry will never be a good experience, so an anti - slip floor would be good.</p>\r\n<p>Another important aspect which most people consider when making their choice is price. After all, this is a utility room where you ordinarily don&rsquo;t bring visitors to, so there&rsquo;s nothing especially spectacular about it. You will therefore reject the luxury options straightaway, because they&rsquo;re unnecessary in a laundry room. You should rather concentrate on practicality.</p>\r\n<h2>What will definitely not be good?</h2>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog9-1.png\" alt=\"Affordable anti-slip floor for laundry room\"></figure>\r\n<p>Probably the worst choice would be carpeting. For one thing, it will always be wet and also the chemicals used to remove stains could damage it. Just pouring a little of it on the floor will create a permanent spot.</p>\r\n<p>Laminate is certainly another floor that doesn&rsquo;t go well for laundry rooms. It&rsquo;s generally known that laminate floors rise because of the action of water. Of course, a drop won&rsquo;t matter, but if the water is standing on the floor for several hours, it will begin to seep in and you can end up having to replace the whole thing.</p>\r\n<p>Not even wood likes water or chemicals. Excessive humidity causes bulging, gaps to open, and the formation of mold. In addition, it amounts to some expensive fund. It&rsquo;s simply not the right choice for places where there is a presence of water.</p>\r\n<h2>Which one is worth considering?</h2>\r\n<p>One of the acceptable options is classic ceramic floor tiles. It handles water beautifully and so is commonly used in bathrooms. It also has a wide range of designs.The problem is its price. It won&rsquo;t be cheap to install it, because per square meter of it costs more than the tile itself.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/business-area.php\">Vinyl flooring</a>&nbsp;is another solution that will save your money. The choice of design is practically as big as for tiles, plus you can choose between classic durable tile or large vinyl tiles. Pay special attention to what&rsquo;s available, because there are different PVC tiles available.</p>\r\n<blockquote>For more details, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/reasons-to-choose-vinyl-flooring.php\">Reasons to choose Vinyl Flooring</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>Because of the dampness, a good anti - slip floor should be considered, one that handles water and chemicals well. Rhino Floor provides the best&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/fortelock.php\">pvc floor tiles</a>&nbsp;with anti - slip patterns, are resistant to chemicals, and are equipped with a system of channels underneath to draw off moisture. The formation of mold is therefore excluded. And if water happens to get underneath it, there&rsquo;s no problem in removing the tiles for a moment, drying the base, and then putting them back in place.</p>\r\n<blockquote>To know more, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/rhino-floor-tiles-in-industrial-use.php\">Where does Rhino Floor Tiles excel in Industrial use?</a></blockquote>\r\n<h2>Do you really want to employ people to make the installation?</h2>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog9-2.png\" alt=\"best options for laundry flooring\