more, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/dirt-trapping-mats.php\">Dirt-Trapping mats - Do you believe in &lsquo;first impression is the best impression&rsquo;?</a></blockquote>\r\n<h2>How does it work?</h2>\r\n<p>The click system entrance mat is composed of&nbsp;<strong>aluminium profiles</strong>&nbsp;with a carpet, brushes, or rubber insert. The combined action of different materials acts as a&nbsp;<strong>dirt barrier</strong>&nbsp;preserving the cleanliness of the buildings&rsquo; floor. It is possible to choose from&nbsp;<strong>several models</strong>&nbsp;with various thicknesses from&nbsp;<strong>Rhino Floor.</strong></p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog11-2.png\" alt=\"dirt barrier entrance mat\"></figure>\r\n<h2>What is the most effective size?</h2>\r\n<p>In general, the bigger the mat is, the more dirt will be removed. 1.5 meters of contact between the entrance mat and the sole of the shoes is enough to ensure proper cleaning.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/\">Floor mats</a>&nbsp;from Rhino Floor covers bigger surfaces, thanks to its click assembly system. There is no limit in the dimension for the walking direction.</p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog11-3.png\" alt=\"entrance matting with dirt barriers\"></figure>\r\n<h2>Advantages of these Entrance floor matting</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>It enhances the aesthetics of the entrance</li>\r\n<li>Can cover surfaces of any shapes</li>\r\n<li>The finishing strips can be replaced easily</li>\r\n<li>The click system is unique, simple and smart</li>\r\n<li>The maintenance is very easy, just by using a vacuum cleaner</li>\r\n<li>The individual aluminium profiles can be changed easily</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<blockquote>Know more at,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/tips-to-choose-the-perfect-entrance-mat.php\">Tips to Choose The Perfect Entrance Mat</a></blockquote>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog11-4.png\" alt=\"floor mats with click system\"></figure>\r\n<p>Do you want your projects to stand out? Choose entrance floor matting with a quick click system from Rhino Floor without a doubt.</p>\r\n<p>Just drop us a mail -&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:sales@rhinofloor.ae\">sales@rhinofloor.ae</a></p>','Entrance floor matting with a click system | dirt barrier','description\" content=\"Learn how to use an entrance mat with a click system to make a great first impression for large entrances with heavy traffic. Available in a wide range of sizes','Entrance floor mat, aluminum entrance mat, floor mat','entrance-floor-matting-with-a-click-system','blogs/entrance-floor-matting-with-a-click-system_default_1704690898.png','Entrance floor matting',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2024-01-08 17:44:59','2024-01-08 17:44:59'),(40,2,'Better to choose a rubber or PVC floor?',NULL,'<h1>Better to choose a rubber or PVC floor?</h1>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog10.png\" alt=\"PVC flooring vs rubber flooring\"></figure>\r\n<p>It mostly depends on where you want to install it and what exactly you expect from it. Both these types have their own specific qualities .Each material looks quite similar at first glance, but don&rsquo;t be fooled. Their composition is different and that\'s what determines their quality. Rubber tiles are made from rubber granulate joined together by polyurethane glue. As its name suggests, the PVC variant is made of polyvinyl chloride (a type of plastic), which is injected into molds.</p>\r\n<h2>Durability and ruggedness</h2>\r\n<p>Rubber flooring is very durable. It can withstand chemicals, cigarette butts, rain, wind and even snow. It can be used for outdoor floor coverings without any issues. The effect of sunshine, however, causes it to fade and lose its original glow over time. By choosing the right thickness, If a greater load comes it can be handled and so it can be used in industrial facilities or in stables for cattle and horses.</p>\r\n<p>Rhino Floor provides the best&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/\">floor tiles in UAE</a>&nbsp;and are not recommended for outdoor usage, but their qualities are better for indoors. Besides withstanding chemicals and cigarette butts, which rubber floors do, PVC can also take heavy loads. They therefore become a good choice for garages where heavy equipment is moved around. A system of drainage channels specially designed, moreover, takes care of excess moisture, and so there is no risk.</p>\r\n<h2>Noise absorption and insulation</h2>\r\n<p>Both materials are comparable in this respect. Rubber and PVC perfectly absorb sound and act as a thermal insulator. Rubber can be slightly more pleasant to stand on, since it is soft, and PVC will be better for moving machines around on. Rhino floor offers a tile pattern that keeps the floor from being slippery. This similarly works for rubber floors, where varieties with non - slip treatment are produced.</p>\r\n<h2>Choice of colors and types</h2>\r\n<p>Rubber tiles are available in different designs; popular is the non-traditional shape as that of a puzzle, the classic square, or rectangular shape. The color scale is far more abundant. Combination of colors can be used to create different patterns on the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Rhino floor offers the best&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/fortelock.php\">PVC floor tiles in UAE</a>&nbsp;. At present, they do not offer a variety of shapes for individual tiles. Their structure was designed by Fortelock to make installation as easy as possible, using interlocks that snap precisely into one another. Color options are broad and so colorful works of art can be created on the floor.</p>\r\n<h2>Complexity of installation</h2>\r\n<p>Rubber tiles with or without contours have different conditions for installation. The first one has a contoured surface on the bottom in order to make it stable on a gravel substrate. The other one is used on a concrete substrate. Understandably, a floor should not be glued to a gravel substrate, so by choosing interlocking tiles, you can easily take them apart whenever needed and assemble them somewhere else. Polyurethane adhesives are usually used for gluing on concrete substrates.</p>\r\n<p>The Rhino Floor PVC floor tiles likewise must not be glued. It&rsquo;s enough to make sure the original surface is even and just assemble the tiles on it. Individual tiles snap into each other nicely; the only thing you need is a rubber hammer and knife. There is another advantage, which also exists for rubber floor tiles &ndash; PVC tiles can be disassembled any time and relocated elsewhere. And if one of the tiles gets damaged, it can be replaced separately.</p>\r\n<h2>Ecology and the impact on the environment</h2>\r\n<p>Here the choice of both is comparable. Rubber tiles can be recycled&ndash;crushed and reused. The same is true with PVC floor tiles, which can be recycled and pressed again. Both variants are eco - friendly and so do not damage the environment or your health. They are made of harmless materials. Modern PVC tiles certainly do not contain any phthalates or other hazardous substances that appear in plastics.</p>\r\n<h2>Where is PVC good and where is the rubber floor?</h2>\r\n<p>Rubber flooring is also good outdoors. It&rsquo;s typically used on playgrounds or in sports halls, because it is soft, so when a child falls, he does not get hurt. People also put them around their pools, on terraces and balconies or as a walkway in the garden. It&rsquo;s therefore clear that they are used outdoors, but nothing prevents you from using them in children&rsquo;s play areas, in warehouses or workshops.</p>\r\n<p>PVC floors are installed only indoors. You will see them very often as the floors of garages, workshops or in large industrial halls. They also look good in the basement, showroom, shop, car service or in the gym.</p>\r\n<p>Both options can be used in many locations without any problems. It only depends on your preference. Is a simple installation and guaranteed durability of 12 years more important than a soft surface and greater choice in the shape of the tiles?</p>\r\n<p>For more details on PVC floor tiles, drop us a mail -&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:sales@rhinofloor.ae\">sales@rhinofloor.ae</a></p>','Better to choose a rubber or PVC floor?','You might not think theres much to choose from, but theres more than you expect. Feel free to choose whether rubber or PVC tile is better for your floor','PVC flooring vs rubber flooring, why to choose pvc over rubber?, benefits of pvc flooring, why is pvc floor better?','better-to-choose-a-rubber-or-pvc-floor','blogs/better-to-choose-a-rubber-or-pvc-floor_default_1704691024.png','UAE floor tiles',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2024-01-08 17:47:06','2024-01-08 17:47:06'),(41,2,'Work-station mats: Always walk on the safer side',NULL,'<h1>Work-station mats: Always walk on the safer side</h1>\r\n<p>Not every workplace is protected from daily dangers: maybe oil drops fall on the ground, liquid spills, leading to high slip risks on floors, making an enormous physical stress for the worker, which remains for a long time on health-related absenteeism in companies. The flooring should be apt for almost every situation in the workplace.</p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog13.png\" alt=\"workstation mats for safety\"></figure>\r\n<p>The Miltex&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/\">floor mats</a>&nbsp;from Rhino Floor are suitable for dry areas where people work for a long time by standing or walking. Some of the applications include assembly stations, laboratories, test rooms, where the work involves more walking.</p>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog13-1.png\" alt=\"ESD workstation mats\"></figure>\r\n<p>The workstation mats from Rhino Floor are developed especially for the use at welding workplaces. The edges of these mats are beveled to reduce trip hazards, the mat provides excellent insulation against cold floors, its non-porous surface 