le.</p>\r\n<p>The flooring in commercial areas should be purposeful, functional and likewise aesthetic. Linoleum or laminate are very common choices. But in comparison with&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/business-area.php\">Vinyl flooring</a>&nbsp;using PVC floor tiles, however, both these options have their own drawbacks.</p>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog3-1.png\" alt=\"Building a small office space\"></figure>\r\n<h2>What might discourage you from linoleum and laminate floors?</h2>\r\n<p>The popular linoleum is made from renewable sources, has a long life, and its appearance does not change. It&rsquo;s available in many designs and thicknesses, the thicker it is, the better is it&rsquo;s quality. But certain problems can arise during installation. The surface must be 100% clean, flat and dry at the time of installation, if not air bubbles can form. Linoleum has expanding and contracting properties,so it can be damaged when installed in high moisture areas. Linoleum is very affordable, starting at 5.07 Euro/m^2 excluding labour cost. But to get high quality, you have to add several hundred per meter square.</p>\r\n<p>Laminate floors are a typical choice for people who yearn for wood but are not affordable on account of the price. You can get laminate anywhere between 7.8 to 39 Euro/m^2, but again you must add in the labor costs. Its big advantage is that it can carry heavy loads and is not damaged by rolling chairs or by weight of heavy furniture. The downside for a business is its poor sound - insulating properties. Every single step of your&rsquo;s will be heard on the floor beneath you.</p>\r\n<blockquote>To know more, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/new-floor-for-temporary-business.php\">Need a new floor for the temporary place you do business in? Try our mobile flooring system</a></blockquote>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog3-2.png\" alt=\"tiles for office space\"></figure>\r\n<h2>Where does Rhino Floor D&eacute;cor tiles excel in this regard?</h2>\r\n<p>Rhino Floor Decor PVC floor tiles currently come in two versions &ndash; Business and Solid. The Business series looks like stone while Solid is reminiscent of classic tiles. They are produced in bright shades so that they do not darken the space and are good for smaller rooms with inadequate light.</p>\r\n<p>In comparison with linoleum and laminate, its big advantage is installation. Rhino Floor&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/fortelock.php\">PVC floor tiles</a>&nbsp;need not be glued instead simply placed, and a system of locks ensure they stay firmly in place. Anyone can install them one after another with nothing more than a rubber hammer. This way saving installation saves costs. Since the tiles are not glued, a damaged piece can be removed anytime and replaced with a new one. Even the entire floor can be taken apart, something appreciated by businesses who are planning to rent their office space and expect to move one day.</p>\r\n<blockquote>For more details, check&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/blog/rhino-floor-tiles-in-industrial-use.php\">Where does Rhino Floor Tiles excel in Industrial use</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>Rhino Floor provides the best&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/\">floor tiles</a>. The properties of these PVC tiles are the same as that of other models. They have a long life, high resistance to wear (even to the movement of rolling chairs) and require no special care. Simply install them and they are ready to go. Don&rsquo;t waste any time with your floor, rather concentrate on your business.</p>\r\n<p>For more details, drop us a mail -&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:sales@rhinofloor.ae\">sales@rhinofloor.ae</a></p>','Building a small office space? Start with the floor!','Ready to break the visual monotony of your office room. Interlocking floor tiles with a system of lock can be chosen over linoleum & laminate floors','Building a small office space, commercial office flooring, tiles for office floor, office flooring, business area flooring, vinyl flooring','building-a-small-office-space-start-with-the-floor','blogs/building-a-small-office-space-start-with-the-floor_default_1704691213.png','UAE floor tiles',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2024-01-08 17:50:14','2024-01-08 17:50:14'),(43,2,'Warehouse and Workshop Floors with Long Service Life',NULL,'<h1>Warehouse and Workshop Floors with Long Service Life</h1>\r\n<figure><img src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog6.png\" alt=\"Warehouse and Workshop floor\"></figure>\r\n<p>The floors of warehouses or workshops are more subjected to the action of&nbsp;<strong>various factors than anywhere else.</strong>&nbsp;In this case, the floor should be resistant to spilled detergents, forklift movements, water or the weight of stored materials.</p>\r\n<p>In these places concrete floors are mainly used, which has its own advantages. If you&rsquo;re looking for something to fit a small shop and you do not need anything special, maybe that&rsquo;s enough. However,&nbsp;<strong>flooring alternatives should be considered</strong>by companies for their large warehouses. PVC floor tiles in workshops and warehouses provide many more opportunities than you might have expected.</p>\r\n<h2>Are you looking for a floor with a longer service life?</h2>\r\n<p>Long service life is usually the most important criterion considered by customers when choosing a floor. If you are looking for such a flooring system, the optimal solution is the PVC floor from Rhino. This model is often used in industrial plants and is also the perfect solution for warehouses where heavy goods are stored. This type of floor accepts heavy loads, for example, four - wheeled trolleys with rubber tires having loads up to 1500 kg. Rhino Floor provides the ideal&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/fortelock.php\">PVC floor tiles</a>, which suits your warehouse, hangar, factory or a smaller workshop. It also has excellent chemical resistance, so you do not have to worry something spills on the floor. Due to the wide range of colors, it allows you to create practical patterns on the floor, ensuring the distinction of different zones and work safety.</p>\r\n<h2>Easy installation of PVC floor tiles</h2>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re planning to set up a workshop, start with the installation of the new floor. In case of concrete, it is a bit more complicated. If you intend to renovate the floor in a workshop or warehouse, you need to make sure that the floor is clean and smooth. At the beginning , we must prepare gravel. Then prepare a clapboard construction made of steel pipes or wooden beams. The concrete is mixed, poured on the floor and smoothed with a polisher. Finally, the floor is sprayed with acrylic resin which reduces water absorption.</p>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog6-1.png\" alt=\"long life warehouse floor\"></figure>\r\n<p>Adapting&nbsp;<a href=\"http://rhinofloor.ae/business-area.php\">Vinyl flooring</a>&nbsp;using PVC tiles it&rsquo;s a lot easier. The first step is the same &ndash; the surface must be smooth and flat, for example, by using self - leveling screeds. Then you can draw lines on the floor by using chalk, get a rubber hammer and get to work. Just place the entire tiles and they will fit into each other perfectly - thanks to their system of locks. After this step, you prepare the rest of the tiles that will be on the edges of the room. This can be easily managed by cutting the tiles with a saw or a cutting knife. In warehouses and workshops where forklift trucks are moving on a daily basis, or there is constantly higher humidity, it i s better to stick tiles to the floor with glue.</p>\r\n<figure><img class=\"space\" src=\"https://www.rhinofloor.ae/images/blog6-2.png\" alt=\"why using PVC tiles for warehouse\"></figure>\r\n<p>In smaller workshops you can carry out the installation without any help, but in large warehouses