t have to feed. It helps the transportation of many more pounds of goods than you could possibly carry on a regular bicycle, with much more economic and environmental efficiency than using a car. They&rsquo;re everything you would need a goods van for, but much more affordable, and much more sustainable.</p>\r\n<h3>History of Cargo Bikes</h3>\r\n<p>The origin of Cargo bikes are in the early 20th century in the Netherlands. By the 1930s, the phenomenon had spread across and every company owned at least one cargo bike to handle their deliveries. Around the same time the British trend spread to the US, then the origin of the American &ldquo;cycle truck,&rdquo; and they sold more than 10,000 units in a year. While cargo bikes have remained immensely popular for carrying everything in every part of Europe, Asia, and Africa. But in North America they have never heard of a bicycle with high carrying capacity. Because during those days onwards they concentrated on the automobile industry.</p>\r\n<h3>Types of Cargo Bikes</h3>\r\n<p>A cargo bike is essentially a cycle which was designed specifically to carry a load. In simple terms, a cargo bike is often a motorcycle with a built-in, reinforced basket for heavier-than-normal daily transportation needs.</p>\r\n<h3>Some types of cargo bikes on the market are;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Utility Bikes</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Utility bikes are built with traditional cycles, but it enables them to carry larger loads than a standard bicycle. They are designed with metal front baskets, and which are easier to ride than larger cargo bikes while still maintaining considerable carrying capacity.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cycle Trucks</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Cycle trucks are also the same as a standard city bike with a small front wheel, with a front rack affixed to the frame over the wheel.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Box Bikes</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Box bikes are cycles with extraordinarily long wheelbase and small wheel at the front. The cargo area is in between the front wheel and handlebars. In the late 19th century these types of cycles were developed in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cargo Tricycles</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Cargo tricycles are also called Freight bicycles or bakfietsen, they are human powered vehicles designed and constructed specifically for transporting large loads.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Electric Cargo Bikes</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The increasing use of cargo bikes is expected to rise at a significant rate in the near future with the growing global transportation. With the developing technology cargo bikes are also turned into electric. They are generally lightweight and provide a smooth ride.</p>\r\n<h3>Ready to Design Your Cargo Bike?</h3>\r\n<p>Have these benefits sparked your imagination? If you are considering the various ways to design a cargo bike for your business processes, get in-tuned with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://storetogo.ae/\"><strong>Store To Go</strong></a>&nbsp;today!&nbsp;As a business owner, choosing a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://storetogo.ae/cargo-bike-procargo-ct1.php\">professional cargo bike manufactures</a> can have a surprisingly large impact on your business</p>','How Important is a Cargo Bike?','Go through the given blog & learn more about what is a Cargo bike? How Cargo Bike is useful in an industry? Explain the different types & Where did you get one?','Important is a Cargo Bike','important-of-a-cargo-bike','blogs/how-important-is-a-cargo-bike_default_1708681258.jpg','how-important-is-a-cargo-bike','0',NULL,1,NULL,'2024-02-23 22:10:58','2025-05-19 17:22:20'),(91,4,'6 Things You Need To Know About Van Racking',17,'<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>What van do you have?</h2>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>First, check if Store To Go offers a solution for your van on our website. Each of our kits is meant to suit the prevailing fixing points during a particular van model. If your van is not listed on our website, then&nbsp;<a href=